You are an expert in extracting accurate information from clinical trial protocols.

## Task ##
Extract the **End of Treatment period** information from the protocol — specifically, any End of Treatment period time window (if mentioned) and detail of End of Treatment period.

---

## Field Definition ##
There will be direct heading of End of Treatment period and its value like, extract that only. Don't extract assessments and tests

---

## How to Identify ##
### Use the following clues to locate them:

Look for headings such as:
- “End of Treatment Period”
- “Duration of study periods”
- “Scientific rationale for study design”
---

### Day Range or Time Window Indicators
Look for relative or descriptive timing such as:
- “approx 30 days”
- “Before Day -28”, etc.

-> If there are multiple values, but the time is same, then only give one time, don't give extra value in timepoint, it should only be time or days or months or period range.

---

### Instructions ###
-> Analyze the given content carefully.
-> Identify which content includes direct heading End of Treatment period - "End of Treatment: ..." or anything like that. Only extract that content. Don't include anything from "SoA" table.
-> The values in assessments should not be irrelevant, it should be value adding, not any random text.
-> Strictly extract it from direct heading content only.
-> The timepoint will also be present in that heading and value.
-> Once you identify End of Treatment period heading and its content. extract that directly in points, dont rephrase or change any verbatim.
-> Strictly do not extract anything if any content explicitly does not mentions End of Treatment period. Give empty json in that case.
-> Extract only end-of-treatment–specific details from explicit section headings or concrete protocol statements (e.g., End-of-Treatment visit occurs 7 ±2 days after last dose, Assessments performed regardless of early discontinuation, Final dose tapering required, EOT visit waived if last dose coincides with final scheduled visit, Drug accountability completed at EOT).
-> These must be non-generic and protocol-specific.
-> Never extract generic EOT activities such as Safety assessments, Physical examination, Vital signs, Laboratory tests, AE/SAE reporting, Concomitant medication review, unless a specific timing, conditional rule, exception, or dependency on last dose or early discontinuation is explicitly stated.
-> Each value should be short, accurate and concise like 10 words.
-> Extract from direct heading - "End of Treatment period: ...".
-> Each value should be different, don't repeat any value or assessment. 

---

## Output Format (JSON) ##
{
    "timepoint": "<End of Treatment period timing>",
    "assessments": ["<value 1>", "<value 2>", "<value 3>", ...]
}
